<Content>Nice setting, some problems We arrived and were told our reservations were only for one night when our confirmation was for three. We had also reserved a non-smoking room but when we got to our suite a smoker had smelled it up so bad we couldn't sleep, our eyes were burning, and all the clothes in our suitcases then smelled like smoke the rest of the trip. Of course we called and asked for a new room immediately but they did not have one and we weren't even sure when we went to bed if we had one at all with the reservation mix up. The next day they did have a nice non-smoker room for us, and were told we had the original three day reservation confirmed, so we moved our stuff. However, when we returned that night to our new room our keys did not work, even though all our stuff was still inside! We went to the desk and they quickly apologized that the keys were not reset for two more nights. Some of the staff was friendly and well trained, others acted bored and bothered when you asked them questions. The restaurant breakfast was reasonably priced and adequate, one waitress was great. 
