<Content>Nice 7 Night Stay My husband and I stayed in a second floor studio suite the week before Christmas on a timeshare exchange. Overall, the accomodations were very nice. The room was equipped with apartment sized appliances- micro, washer/dryer, dishwasher. The bath was tiled in marble and the room was nicely decorated in a Southwesten style. The deck was furnished with comfortable lounge chairs and offered a view of the 17th fairway. Unfortunately, neither of us slept well during our stay. The king sized bed was much too firm and the refriderator was rather noisy.  We paid $59 each to play the challenging championship course. It was in good condition and the staff was courteous and accomodationg. One afternoon we spent several hours using the practice facility for $15 each. The driving range was stocked with ample range balls and the putting and chipping greens were spacious and well manicured. 
